# rotate each and every row in the dataset.
rotate_df <- function(df_vec, nrow = 64, ncol = 64) {
  df_matrix <- matrix(df_vec, nrow = nrow, byrow = T)
  df_rotated <- t(df_matrix)[, ncol:1]
  return(as.vector(t(df_rotated)))
}
df <- t(apply(X_df, 1, rotate_df))
dim(df)

Find the owner for new.csv

Plot the new face with the corresponding projection coefficients, and find the most similar faces from the database.

new <-read.csv("C:/Users/62666/Desktop/Spring 2023/DA 350/week12/new.csv", header = T)

ID <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = 400, nrow = 400))
for (i in 1:400) {
  coel <- df[i,] %*% eigenfaces
  ID[i,] <- coel
}
new_df <- t(new) - AVF2
new_ID <- new_df %*% eigenfaces
distances <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = 1, nrow = 400))
for (i in 1:400) {
  distances[i,] <- apply(new_ID, 1, function(x) sqrt(sum((x - ID[i,])^2)))
}
#first 10 distances between new photo and df
distances[1:10,]
##  [1]  9.889909 12.536645 10.654530 13.359319 11.499292 11.750737  9.220720
##  [8] 10.418606 10.412971 12.495616
colnames(distances)[1] <- "distance"
which.min(distances$distance)
